Date: Wed, 1 Apr 2026 14:29:16 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?opencl:=20flash=20attention=20optimizations=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20BLOCK=5FN=3D64,=20N=5FSPLIT,=20native=20exp,=20quan?=
 =?UTF-8?q?tized=20KV=20cache?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Improve flash attention kernel performance across all head-dimension configs:

Kernel changes (flash_attn_f32_f16.cl):
- BLOCK_M=64 for DK<=128: fills one wavefront (was 32 = 50% utilisation)
- BLOCK_N=64 for DK=64: halves serial KV-tile count at PP4096 (128→64)
- N_SPLIT=2 for DK=80-128: two threads share each query's dot-product,
  halving register pressure; threshold=0 always uses split for prefill
- N_SPLIT=4 for DK=256: BLOCK_M=32/N_SPLIT=4 vs old BLOCK_M=16/N_SPLIT=8
  — 2× more queries share each KV tile, halving effective KV bandwidth
- native exp() instead of exp() — exploits GPU fast-math path
- j+=4 softmax unroll in the inner accumulation loop

Prepass kernel (flash_attn_pre_f16.cl, new):
- flash_attn_kv_pad_f16: pads KV tensors to BLOCK_N boundary in fp16
- flash_attn_mask_pad_f16: pads attention mask to match padded KV length
- flash_attn_blk_f16: precomputes per-block mask skip flags to short-circuit
  fully-masked KV tiles without loading them

Dispatch changes (ggml-opencl.cpp):
- Choose N_SPLIT>1 "split" kernel vs baseline based on n_kv threshold
- Run KV-pad and mask-pad prepasses when n_kv % BLOCK_N != 0
- Run blk prepass when a mask is present; retry blk buffer alloc after
  clFinish on OOM (handles driver deferred-dealloc lag)
- Support quantized KV cache: dequantize Q4_0/Q8_0 KV tensors to fp16
  via CPU round-trip into a temporary GPU buffer before FA dispatch

Performance on Adreno (Snapdragon X Elite, Adreno X1-85):
- FA=1 now matches or exceeds FA=0 for DK=64/96/128 at all PP sizes
- DK=256: FA=1 PP4096 92% of FA=0 (was 40%)
- DK=192 (Gemma-2): FA=1 PP4096 94% of FA=0
